nano.remexp.broadcaster.locks
Class LockHolder

java.lang.Object
  nano.remexp.broadcaster.locks.LockHolder
Direct Known Subclasses:
AutoApproachLock, CalibrateStageLock, CamAngleLock, GotoLock, MoveTipLock, NoLock, ScanningLock, ScanRangeLock, WithdrawLock
public abstract class LockHolder
extends java.lang.Object

The interface for the locks that are being linked with commands to the remote experiment. As soon as the broadcaster receives such a valid command it sets the lock for it and waits for the appropriate reply of the remote experiment. In any case there is also a time out on each lock after which the lock will be released anyways. Abort actions can be defined in case a locking action should be able to be aborted.

Version:
1.1 23.08.2012
Author:
Dominic Bosch

resolveLock

public LockHolder resolveLock(java.lang.String msg)
If the remote experiment sends messages and there is a LockHolder locking the remote experiment, those messages are being parsed through this method of the appropriate LockHolder. Through defining another Lock in the resolveLock method of the first one, it is possible to have lock chains, waiting for different commands in a row to arrive.

Parameters:
msg - The message sent by the remote experiment
Returns:
The LockHolder that now holds the lock or null if the lock is released again.
